description: Latin aneticus, from Ancient Greek ἀνετικός (anetikós, “relaxing, remitting”), from ἄνεσις (ánesis, “relaxation, abatement”).

adjectives.description: anetic (comparative more anetic, superlative most anetic)

entries.meaning: (medicine, obsolete, rare) Soothing; helping to relieve a malady.
